title: Definitely up there, Foley says of win over England
text:
Definitely up there, Foley says of win over England 3:36pm BST - 00:26 
Flyhalf scored 28 of his team's 33 points in host's defeat ▲ Hide Transcript ▶ View Transcript 
SHOWS: LONDON, ENGLAND, UNITED KINGDOM (OCTOBER 5, 2015) (ARU MEDIA - EDITORIAL USE ONLY) 1. AUSTRALIA TEAM TRAINING, BERNARD FOLEY SEEN 2. (SOUNDBITE) (English) BERNARD FOLEY, ASKED ABOUT IMPORTANCE OF WIN OVER ENGLAND, SAYS: "It's definitely up there, to take any win and to beat England at Twickenham, it's the first time I've done that so that's definitely high in prizes and achievements in my test career." STORY: Having had a day to digest their dismantling of the hosts with a dominant performance at Twickenham, the Wallabies on Monday (October 5) had time to reflect on the importance of their victory before turning their focus to Saturday's (October 10) Pool A decider against Wales. Australia's flyhalf Bernard Foley scored 28 of his team's 33 points, and was asked by reporters to rate the win against England. "It's definitely up there, to take any win and to beat England at Twickenham, it's the first time I've done that so that's definitely high in prizes and achievements in my test career," he said.
